# LibraryManagementSystem-Java

A simple command-line Library Management application written in Java to demonstrate OOP concepts: inheritance, method overriding, polymorphism (upcasting & downcasting), and usage of collections.

## Features
- Add book (Story or Subject)
- Remove book by name
- Search book by name
- Sort books by price (descending)
- Display all books
- Calculate total price

## Files
- Book.java
- Story.java
- Subject.java
- Library.java
- LibraryManagement.java

## Run
```bash
javac *.java
java LibraryManagement
Notes
Input prompts are interactive via Scanner.

Upcasting is used to store Story/Subject in a single List<Book>.

Downcasting is used when printing subclass-specific details.
